The '''Society for Political Methodology''' is a [[learned society]] focused on quantitative methods in [[political science]], and an organized section of the [[American Political Science Association]]. Founded in 1983, it publishes –- via [[Oxford University Press]] – the peer-reviewed journal ''[[Political Analysis (journal)|Political Analysis]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Political Analysis|url=https://www.jstor.org/journal/polianalysis|website=jstor.org|publisher=[[JSTOR]]|accessdate=February 19, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=About|url=https://www.cambridge.org/core/membership/spm/about-us|website=cambridge.org|publisher=[[Cambridge University Press]]|accessdate=February 19, 2018}}</ref> The society annually awards the John T. Williams Dissertation Prize for the best dissertation proposal in the area of political methodology.<ref>{{cite news|title=Building analytical tools to improve understanding of China's political economy|url=http://news.mit.edu/2015/yiqing-xu-building-analytical-tools-political-economics-china-1215|accessdate=February 19, 2018|work=MIT News|date=December 15, 2015}}</ref>

